# LeakSanitizer suppressions for the libregnum test suite.
#
# This is a starter file, wired in via LSAN_OPTIONS=suppressions= in the
# run-sanitize target of tests/Makefile. Only suppress leaks confirmed to be
# benign process-lifetime / singleton / tooling noise -- never suppress a
# real libregnum leak. See docs/building.org "Testing & Memory Checking".
#
# LSan suppression syntax: a line `leak:<regex>` suppresses any leak whose
# symbolized stack trace contains a frame matching <regex>. (This is the
# LSan suppression format -- distinct from ASan's interceptor suppressions,
# which use types like interceptor_name and do NOT accept `leak:`.)
#
# To triage a single binary, e.g.:
#   LSAN_OPTIONS="suppressions=$(pwd)/lsan.supp" \
#     ASAN_OPTIONS="detect_leaks=1" \
#     build/sanitize/tests/test-foo --tap

# LrgCrashReporter is a process-lifetime singleton obtained via
# lrg_crash_reporter_get_default(); it (and its init-time GHashTable) are
# intentionally never released. test-crash exercises it directly.
leak:lrg_crash_reporter_get_default